<SUBJECT>买票</SUBJECT>
<TEXT>
前几日在书店见到一本书《荆棘鸟》（ The Thorn Birds），是英文原   
版，早在大学的时候就读过这本书的中文版，那时我就相信那种至死不渝、   
无怨无悔的爱，尽管其间许多沧桑变故，两人始终不能走到一起。   

    这本书的序言象征了整个故事的主题，读来很令人感动：   

    There is a legend about a bird which sings just once in its  
life, more　sweetly than any other creature on the face of the  
earth. From the moment it leaves the nest it searches for a thorn  
tree, and does not rest until it has found once.  

    Then, singing among the savage branches, it impales itself  
upon the longest, sharpest spine. And, dying, it rises above its  
own agony to outcarol the lark and the nightingales.  

    One superlative song, existence the price. But the whole world  
stills to listen, and God in His heaven smiles. For the best is  
only bought at the cost of great pain…… Or so says the legend.  

    那是一个美丽哀伤极致的传说。其实一生中能拥有这份爱就足够了，而   

无谓形式和结果的。一生能这么无怨无悔地爱着，又何尝不是一种幸福。   

    在时光流逝、命运无常里，还能说什么是对、什么是错呢？一颗平常心   
是多么重要！
</TEXT>
</DOC>

